{[showcards S:CT]

You are South. The bidding has been as shown. You led the \S5, North plays the \ST and East wins the \SK. To the second trick East plays the \CT and you must discard something. 

Play the \SJ.

You know that North has no high \S honor or he would have played it to the first trick. So East has the \S A Q left, plus all those \C tricks. You need to have South switch to a \H if possible.

North must be expecting to lead a \S back when he wins the \CQ which you hope he holds. Your \SJ discard may make him rethink. If your \Ss were any good why would you be discarding a winner when all you had to do was toss a small red card?

Hopefully North will come to the conclusion that this is Suit Preference for a \H return and will play his \HJ. Hopefully.}
[Play "W"]S5

